value.value: Closure whereby a measured quantity of the contents is released by actuation of the valve.
A mobile thermally insulated container designed to maintain the contents in a liquid state.

Release of the substance(s) in a way that differs from that which would be achieved with a conventional-release product, which is achieved by a special formulation design and/or manufacturing method, but which is not classified as delayed-release or prolonged-release; pulsatile-release products are included.

Solid single-dose preparation consisting of a hard shell containing a solid or semi-solid formulation, showing a rate, a place and/or a time of release different from that of a conventional-release capsule. This deliberate modification is achieved by a special formulation design and/or manufacturing method.

Solid single-dose preparation consisting of a soft shell containing a semi-solid or liquid formulation, showing a rate, a place and/or a time of release different from that of a conventional-release capsule. This deliberate modification is achieved by a special formulation design and/or manufacturing method.

Solid preparation consisting of granules showing a rate and/or place of release different from that of conventional-release granules. This deliberate modification is achieved by a special formulation design and/or manufacturing method. Modified-release granules are usually single-dose preparations intended for oral use, and include prolonged-release, delayed release and pulsatile-release granules.

label.value: Modified-release Granule for Oral Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation consisting of modified-release granules intended to be dispersed in the specified liquid to obtain an oral suspension.
Aid used for the administration or inhalation of a medicinal product by mouth.

label.value: Mouthwash, Powder for Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation consisting of one or more powders intended to be dissolved in the specified liquid to obtain a mouthwash.

label.value: Mouthwash, Tablet for Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation consisting of an uncoated tablet intended to be dissolved in water to obtain a mouthwash.

Solid single-dose preparation to be applied to the buccal mucosa to obtain a systemic delivery over an extended period of time. Mucoadhesive buccal tablets are usually prepared by compression of mixtures of powders or granulations into tablets with a shape suited for the intended use. They usually contain hydrophilic polymers, which on wetting with saliva produce a flexible hydrogel that adheres to the buccal mucosa.
Multidose container with an integral pump designed to protect the contents against in use-contamination.
Multidose container with integral metering pump.
Multidose container with an integral pump. Metering pump, spray pump, and multidose container with airless pump are excluded.
Device for puncturing the skin, normally used for immunological products, especially diagnostics.
Aid used for the administration of a drug by nose.
Liquid single-dose or multidose preparation consisting of an emulsion intended for nasal use by means of a suitable applicator.

label.value: Nasal Drops, Lyophilisate and Solvent for Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Lyophilisate and solvent intended for the preparation of nasal drops, suspension, for veterinary use, by dispersing the lyophilisate in the solvent.

label.value: Nasal Drops, Lyophilisate for Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation for veterinary use consisting of a freeze-dried powder intended to be dispersed in the specified liquid to obtain a suspension for use as nasal drops.

label.value: Nasal Drops, Powder and Solvent for Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Powder and solvent intended for the preparation of nasal drops, solution, by dissolving the powder in the solvent.

label.value: Nasal Drops, Powder for Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation consisting of one or more powders intended to be dissolved in the specified liquid to obtain a nasal drops solution.

label.value: Nasal Drops, Solution in Single-dose Container Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a nasal drops solution presented in a single-dose container.

Liquid single-dose or multidose preparation consisting of an emulsion in a container with or without a metering dose valve or in a container with a spray pump or equivalent device to create a spray, intended for nasal use.

label.value: Nasal Spray, Lyophilisate and Solvent for Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Lyophilisate and solvent intended for the preparation of a nasal spray, suspension, for veterinary use, by dispersing the lyophilisate in the solvent.

label.value: Nasal Spray, Lyophilisate for Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation consisting of a freeze-dried powder intended to be dispersed in the specified liquid to obtain a nasal spray, suspension.

label.value: Nasal Spray, Powder for Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation consisting of one or more powders intended to be dissolved in the specified liquid to obtain a nasal spray solution.

Liquid single-dose or multidose preparation consisting of a solution in a container with or without a metering dose valve or in a container with a spray pump or equivalent device to create a spray, intended for nasal use.

label.value: Nasal Spray, Solution in Single-dose Container Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a nasal spray solution presented in a single-dose container.

label.value: Nasal Spray, Solution/Oromucosal Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of a solution intended for use as a nasal spray or an oromucosal solution.

Liquid single-dose or multidose preparation consisting of a suspension in a container with or without a metering dose valve or in a container with a spray pump or equivalent device to create a spray, intended for nasal use.
Solid single-dose preparation, usually rod-shaped or conical, intended for nasal use to obtain a local effect.
Liquid single-dose or multidose preparation consisting of usually an aqueous isotonic solution intended for cleansing the nasal cavities.
Liquid preparation consisting of a solution intended for nasal or oromucosal application.
Liquid preparation consisting of a solution in a container with or without a metering dose valve or in a container with a spray pump, intended for nasal or oromucosal use.
Liquid preparation consisting of a solution intended for conversion by nebulizers into an aerosol.
Administration of medicinal product converted into an aerosol.

Liquid preparation consisting of an emulsion intended for inhalation to obtain local effect or systemic delivery. The emulsion is converted into an aerosol by a continuously operating nebulizer or a metered-dose nebulizer.
Liquid preparation consisting of a solution intended for inhalation use. The solution is converted into an aerosol by a continuously operating nebulizer or a metered-dose nebulizer.
Liquid preparation consisting of a suspension intended for inhalation use. The suspension is converted into an aerosol by a continuously operating nebulizer or a metered-dose nebulizer.
Device for injecting a medicinal product, usually a liquid, by means of high pressure without a needle, through the skin barrier.
No transformation of the product takes place.
The technique of administration of a pharmaceutical product by an unspecified method.
Relating to the eyes and nares of a bird as the intended site of administration.
Liquid, usually multidose preparation for veterinary use consisting of a suspension intended for oculonasal use.

Solid sterile preparation of suitable size and shape, designed to be inserted in the conjunctival sac to produce a local or ocular effect by the release of active substance(s) over a determined period of time. Ophthalmic inserts generally consist of a reservoir of active substance(s) embedded in a matrix or bounded by a rate-controlling membrane. They are presented individually in sterile containers.
